        <Text textformat="02"><![CDATA[<p>When Aoife Brennan-Walsh inherited her family's West Cork farm, she also inherited four generations of decisions about land, soil, and cattle. <em>The Carbon Inheritance</em> is the story of what she did next — and what it cost her.</p><p>Part memoir, part investigation, this book traces the invisible carbon ledger running through one Irish family and asks the question every farming family in Britain and Ireland is quietly avoiding: what do we owe the land we will one day hand on?</p><p><strong>'Urgent, honest, and beautifully observed'</strong> — Robert Macfarlane</p>]]></Text>
